ProjectsArray.Title: Project 1: Wug Bot 3.0 using Python and NLTK
ProjectsArray.About: I am co-developing Wug Bot 3.0, a linguistics-focused Discord bot capable of performing various linguistic analyses. This bot supports morphological, phonetic (IPA), syntactic, and semantic processing of sentences. It leverages the Natural Language Toolkit (NLTK) for linguistic data processing, WordNet for enhanced semantic analysis, and the ArgosTranslate library to facilitate translations across 13 languages, with plans to support additional languages in the near future.
ProjectsArray.About1: The bot provides detailed insights into word structures, including morphemes, roots, and affixes, while also tracking morphological processes like inflectional changes. By combining linguistic rigor with multilingual functionality, Wug Bot 3.0 aims to serve as a robust tool for language enthusiasts, educators, and researchers. Future updates will expand its capabilities and make it even more versatile for complex linguistic tasks.

ProjectsArray.Title: Project 2: Using Different Machine Learning Models to Predict Whether a Hotel Booking Will be Canceled or Not
ProjectsArray.About: After experimenting with different ML models, a model called RandomForest gets this job done accurately. It fits a decision tree classifiers on various sub-samples of the Hotel Booking dataset, and then averaging to improve its predictive accuracy and control over-fitting. Since the dataset is huge, roughly 69k samples, this model is accurate because it constructs multiple decision trees at the same training time. Lastly, it handles non-linearly data well. As a result, the model got an accuracy of roughly 88% to predict whether a hotel booking will be canceled or not!

ProjectsArray.Title: Project 3: Recommender System using C++.
ProjectsArray.About: It can recommend up to 100k movies based on its user and movie databases. I used unordered hash map, vectors and an algorithm called Tree Multimap to sort the movie and users from its respective databases and gather recommendations from them based on a certain criteria. So the complexities can range from different kinds of directors, genres, actors, e.g O(Log(D)) to O(log(A))

ProjectsArray.Title: Project 4: EXT2 Filesystem in C
ProjectsArray.About: Implemented a EXT2 Filesystem in C so that the kernal could mount it. This is a 1 MiB EXT2 FS with 1000 sized blocks and has a space for 128 inodes. It has 4 inodes: the root directory, lost+found directory, 1 regular file called hello+world, and 1 symbolic link that points to hello+world called hello.
